State coverage is uneven in a specific way: the high-level lists usually have loading/error/empty branches, while several composed portal pages pass only `loading` into child components and never surface query errors. The core generation action is weaker still: it changes one button label during computation, with no staged wait narrative or progress feedback. I’m validating the artifact, mobile, accessibility, and cache layers next so the recommendations connect across the whole experience.
